          <h6>General Catalog, 2009-11</h6>
          <p>&quot;I came to Berkeley as a naive adolescent and still remember 
            the exhilaration on first reading the Berkeley catalog, which seemed 
            to me the size of a telephone book, containing unbelievably attractive 
            travel invitations to new intellectual worlds.&quot;<br>
            <strong>&#8212; Daniel Koshland, Jr., '41, Professor emeritus 
            of Biochemistry</strong> </p>
